Description: Fragment of oval handle of a probably Rhodian pottery transport amphora to moderate turn. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 102, 3. Name Onasimos. There are several similar dies.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1589)
